==Old English==
===Etymology===
From West Germanic: cognate with Old Frisian [[festna]], Old Saxon [[fastnon]], Old High German [[fastnion|fastniōn]] (German [[fesitgen]] ‘solidify’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'fæstnian/

===Verb===
(ġe)'''fæstnian''' (class 2 weak: '''fæstnaþ''' ‘he fastens’, '''fæstnode''' ‘he fastened’, '''fæstnodon''' ‘they fastened’, ('''ġe''')'''fæstnod''' past participle)
# to [[fasten]] or [[fix]]; to [[establish]]

